atu PII PP. IX (1846) usque ad Pontificatum Leonis PP. XIII (1903)|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=5oXUjwEACAAJ|year=1978|volume=Volume VIII|publisher=Il Messaggero di S. Antonio|language=Latin}}\n*{{cite book|last= Pi\u0119ta|first=Zenon|title=Hierarchia catholica medii et recentioris aevi...  A pontificatu Pii PP. X (1903) usque ad pontificatum Benedictii PP. XV (1922)|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=QXuJQwAACAAJ|volume=Volume IX|year=2002|publisher=Messagero di San Antonio|location=Padua|language=Latin|isbn=978-88-250-1000-8}}\n\n===Studies===\n*{{cite book|last=Cappelletti|first=Giuseppe|title=Le chiese d'Italia|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=mdICAAAAQAAJ|volume=Volume sesto (6)|year=1847|publisher=G. Antonelli|location=Venezia|language=Italian|pages=271\u2013385}}\n*{{cite book|last=Kehr|first=Paulus Fridolinus|title=Italia pontificia: Latium|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=-vdeO8HJ6g4C&pg=PA135|volume=Vol. II|year=1907|publisher=Apud Weidmannos|location=Berlin|language=Latin|pages=135\u2013145}}\n* Lanzoni, Francesco (1927). ''[https://archive.org/stream/MN5017ucmf_0#page/n281/mode/2up Le diocesi d'Italia dalle origini al principio del secolo VII (an. 604)]''. Faenza: F. Lega, pp.&nbsp; 166-167. {{in lang|it}}\n*Schwartz, Gerhard (1907). [https://archive.org/details/MN42020ucmf_1 ''Die Besetzung der Bist\u00fcmer Reichsitaliens unter den s\u00e4chsischen und salischen Kaisern: mit den Listen der Bisch\u00f6fe, 951-1122'']. Leipzig: B.G. Teubner. pp. 268-269.{{in lang|de}}\n*{{cite book|last1=Ughelli|first1=Ferdinando|last2=Coleti|first2=Niccol\u00f2|title=Italia sacra, sive De Episcopis Italiae|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=zTkOnHgYhFgC|volume=Tomus primus|edition=secunda|year=1717|publisher=apud Sebastianum Coleti|location=Venice|language=Latin|pages=305\u2013324}}\n\n\n\n{{Roman Catholic Ecclesiastical Province of Rome}}\n{{coord missing|Italy}}\n\n[[Category:Roman Catholic dioceses in Lazio|Anagni]]\n[[Category:Bishops of Anagni]]\n[[Category:Dioceses established in the 5th century|Anagni]]\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Roman_Catholic_Diocese_of_Anagni-Alatri"}
{"title_page": "Roman Catholic Diocese of Amarillo", "text_new": "{{Infobox diocese\n| jurisdiction      = Diocese<!-- Type of jurisdiction: i.e. Diocese or Archdiocese -->\n| name              = Amarillo\n| latin             = Dioecesis Amarillensis\n| local             = <!-- Name in the native language --> \n| image             = File:Coat of Arms Diocese of Amarillo, TX.svg\n| image_size        = 175px \n| image_alt         = \n| caption           = \n<!---- Locations ---->\n| country           = {{flag|United States of America}}\n| territory         = Panhandle of Texas\n| province          = [[List of the Roman Catholic dioceses of the United States#Ecclesiastical province of San Antonio|Province of San Antonio]]\n| coordinates       = <!-- Use {{coord}} --> \n<!---- Statistics ---->\n| area_sqmi         = 25,800<!-- Area in square miles, automatically converted -->\n| population        = 427,927\n| population_as_of  = 2012\n| catholics         = 50,237<!-- Number of Catholics in the diocese -->\n| catholics_percent = 11.7\n| parishes          = 38<!-- Number of parishes in the diocese -->\n| churches          = <!-- Number of churches in the diocese -->\n| congregations     = <!-- Number of congregations in the diocese -->\n| schools           = <!-- Number of church supported schools in the diocese -->\n| members           = <!-- Number of members in the diocese -->\n<!---- Information ---->\n| denomination      = [[Roman Catholic]]\n| rite              = [[Roman Rite]]\n| established       = August 3, 1926\n| cathedral         = [[St. Mary's Cathedral (Amarillo, Texas)|St. Mary's Cathedral]]\n| cocathedral       = \n| patron            = \n| priests           = <!-- Number of priests in the diocese -->\n<!---- Current leadership ---->\n| pope              = {{Incumbent pope}} <!-- DO NOT CHANGE. This will update the Popes Automatically as they change -->\n| bishop            = [[Patrick Zurek]]<br>Bishop of Amarillo\n| metro_archbishop  = [[Gustavo Garcia-Siller]]<br>Archbishop of San Antonio\n| coadjutor         = \n| auxiliary_bishops = \n| vicar_general     = \n| emeritus_bishops  = [[John Walter Yanta]]\n<!---- Map ---->\n| map               = Diocese of Amarillo in Texas.jpg\n| map_alt           = \n| map_caption       = \n<!---- Website ---->\n| website           = [http://www.amarillodiocese.org/ amarillodiocese.org]\n| footnotes         = \n}}\nThe '''Roman Catholic Diocese of Amarillo''' ({{lang-la|Dioecesis Amarillensis}}) is a [[Roman Catholic]] [[diocese]] in [[Amarillo, Texas|Amarillo]], [[Texas]]. It was founded on August 3, 1926 out of territory taken from the Diocese of Dallas<ref name= Dallas>{{cite web|url=https://www.cathdal.org/DioceseofDallasHistory.pdf |title= History of the Diocese of Dallas |publisher= Diocess of Dallas|accessdate=2016-11-07|last=|first=}}</ref> and the Diocese of San Antonio on the same day that the [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of San Antonio]], its [[metropolitan bishop|metropolitan see]], was elevated to metropolitan status, replacing [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of New Orleans|New Orleans]].<ref name= Hierarchy>{{cite web|url= http://www.catholic-hierarchy.org/diocese/damar.html|title= Diocese of Amarillo |publisher= Catholic-Hierarchy|accessdate=2016-11-07|last=|first=}}</ref>\n\n==Bishops==\n\n===Bishops of Amarillo===\nThe list of bishops and their terms of service:\n# [[Rudolph Gerken]] (1926&ndash;1933), appointed [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Santa Fe|Archbishop of Santa Fe]]\n# [[Robert Emmet Lucey]] (1934&ndash;1941), appointed [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of San Antonio|Archbishop of San Antonio]]\n# [[Laurence Julius FitzSimon]] (1941&ndash;1958)\n# [[John Louis Morkovsky]] (1958&ndash;1963), appointed [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Galveston-Houston|Bishop of Galveston-Houston]]\n# [[Lawrence Michael De Falco]] (1963&ndash;1979)\n# [[Leroy Matthiesen|Leroy Theodore Matthiesen]] (1980&ndash;1997)\n# [[John Walter Yanta]] (1997&ndash;2008)\n# [[Patrick Zurek]] (2008&ndash;present)\n\n===Other priest of the diocese who became a bishop===\n* [[Thomas Joseph Drury]], appointed [[Roman Catholic Diocese of San Angelo|Bishop of San Angelo]] in 1961 and later [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Corpus Christi|Bishop of Corpus Christi]]\n\n==High schools==\n* [[Holy Cross Catholic Academy (Amarillo, Texas)|Holy Cross Catholic Academy]], Amarillo\n\n==Former Cathedrals==\n*[[Sacred Heart Cathedral (Amarillo, Texas)]], 1927-1975\n*[[St. Laurence Catholic Church (Amarillo, Texas)]], 1975-2011\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Catholicism}}\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n* [[Catholic Church by country]]\n* [[Catholic Church in the United States]]\n* [[List of the Catholic dioceses of the United States#Ecclesiastical province of San Antonio|Ecclesiastical Province of San Antonio]]\n* [[Global organisation of the Catholic Church]]\n* [[List of Roman Catholic archdioceses]] (by country and continent)\n* [[List of Roman Catholic dioceses (alphabetical)]] (including archdioceses)\n* [[List of Roman Catholic dioceses (structured view)]] (including archdioceses)\n* [[List of the Catholic dioceses of the United States]]\n{{div col end}}\n<!-- please keep entries in alphabetical order -->\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.amarillodiocese.org/ Roman Catholic Diocese of Amarillo Official Site]\n\n{{coord|35|11|57|N|101|50|43|W|source:plwiki|display=title}}\n\n{{Roman Catholic Diocese of Amarillo}}\n{{Roman Catholic Ecclesiastical Province of San Antonio}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Roman Catholic Diocese of Amarillo| ]]\n[[Category:Christian organizations established in 1926]]\n[[Category:Culture of Amarillo, Texas]]\n[[Category:Roman Catholic dioceses and prelatures established in the 20th century|Amarillo]]\n[[Category:Roman Catholic dioceses in the United States|Amarillo]]\n[[Category:1926 establishments in Texas]]\n\n\n{{US-RC-diocese-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox diocese\n| jurisdiction      = Diocese<!-- Type 