his will update the Popes Automatically as they change -->\n| bishop_title      = Bishop\n| bishop            = [[Mario Paciello]]\n| coadjutor         = \n| auxiliary_bishops = \n| vicar_general     = \n| emeritus_bishops  = \n<!---- Map ---->\n| map               = Roman Catholic Diocese of Altamura in Italy.jpg\n| map_alt           = Locator map for diocese of Altamura\n| map_caption       = \n<!---- Website ---->\n| website           = \n| footnotes         = [http://www.diocesidialtamura.it/ www.diocesidialtamura.it]\n}}\n\nThe  '''Diocese of Altamura-Gravina-Acquaviva delle Fonti''' ({{lang-la|Dioecesis Altamurensis-Gravinensis-Aquavievensis}}) is a Roman Catholic [[diocese]] in [[Apulia]], southern Italy, created in 1986. In that year, the '''territorial prelature of Altamura e Acquaviva delle Fonti''' was united with the [[diocese of Gravina]]. The present diocese is a [[suffragan]] of the [[archdiocese of Bari-Bitonto]].<ref name=CathHierAltGravAcq>[http://www.catholic-hierarchy.org/diocese/dagaf.html \"Diocese of Altamura-Gravina-Acquaviva delle Fonti\"] ''[[Catholic-Hierarchy.org]]''. David M. Cheney. Retrieved September 30, 2016.{{Self-published inline|date=March 2017}}</ref><ref name=GCathAltGravAcq>[http://www.gcatholic.org/dioceses/diocese/alta0.htm \"Diocese of Altamura-Gravina-Acquaviva delle Fonti\"] ''GCatholic.org''. Gabriel Chow. Retrieved September 30, 2016.{{Self-published inline|date=March 2017}}</ref>\n\nThe seat of the bishop is at [[Altamura Cathedral]], with [[Acquaviva Cathedral]] and [[Gravina Cathedral]] as [[co-cathedral]]s.\n\n==History==\n\n[[Altamura]] was once a [[territorial prelature]]: an [[archipresbyterate]], declared exempt from episcopal jurisdiction by [[Pope Innocent IV]] in 1248, and again by [[Pope Innocent VIII]] (1484\u201392). [[Acquaviva delle Fonti]], a town of the Campagna, was declared similarly exempt by [[Pope Pius IX]] and united with Altamura on 17 August 1848.<ref>[http://www.newadvent.org/cathen/01345b.htm ''Catholic Encyclopedia'' article]</ref>\n\n==Prelates and Bishops==\n===Territorial Prelature of Altamura===\n''Erected: 1248''<br>\n''Latin Name: Altamurensis''\n:'''...'''\n*Pietro de Moreriis (1296 \u2013 c. 1308?)<ref>Pietro de Angeriaco was appointed by [[Charles II of Naples|Charles II of Anjou, King of Naples]] 1285\u20131309) in 1296. Charles II had successfully petitioned [[Pope Boniface VIII]] to unite the two offices of Treasurer of S. Nicholas in Bari and Archpriest of Altamura.  {{cite book|author=Antonio Beatillo|title=Historia della vita, miracoli, traslatione, e gloria dell'illustrissimo confessore di Christo San Nicol\u00f2 il Magno Arcivescovo di Mira|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=i0ZMAAAAcAAJ&pg=RA2-PA460|year=1703|publisher=Pietro Olivieri|location=Roma|language=Italian|page=460}} Serena, pp. 330-331.</ref>\n:'''...'''\n*Giovanni Geronimo de Mari (attested 1606\u20131607)<ref>{{cite book|author=Bartolomeo Chioccarelli|title=Archivio della reggia giurisdizione del regno di Napoli, ristretto in indice compendioso ...|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=tKhFAAAAcAAJ&pg=RA1-PA32|year=1721|location=Vinezia|language=Italian|pages=26\u201334; 132\u2013134}}</ref>\n:'''...'''\n*Giandomenico Falcone (1 June 1842 \u2013 10 July 1858 \u2013 24 December 1862)<ref>Canon Falcone had been Vicar General of Molfetta before being named Archpriest of Acquaviva on 1 June 1842 by King Ferdinand II of Naples. {{cite book|last=Michele Garruba|first=|title=Serie critica de sacri pastori Baresi, corr. accresciuta ed ill|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=nldcAAAAcAAJ&pg=PA42|year=1844|publisher=Cannone|location=Bari|language=Italian|pages=711\u2013712}}  To this was added the office of Archpriest of Altamura on 16 October 1858: {{cite book|title=Almanacco reale del regno delle Due Sicilie|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Y6BjAAAAcAAJ&pg=PA176|year=1854|publisher=Stamperia Reale|location=Napoli|language=Italian|page=176}} On 10 July 1858 Falcone was named titular Bishop of Eumeneia: {{cite book|title=La civilt\u00e0 cattolica: pubblicazione periodica per tutta l'Italia|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=B9E0V4Pxh9AC&pg=PA229|series=Terza serie|volume=Vol. 11|year=1858|publisher=Uffizio della civilta cattolica|location=Roma|language=Italian|page=229}} Serena, p. 334.</ref>\n:''Sede Vacante'' (24 December 1862 \u2013 28 August 1879)\n*Luigi Marcello Pellegrini (1879\u20131894 Died)<ref>In May 1881 Pellegrini was appointed titular Bishop of Troas (Turkey). Serena, p. 334.</ref>\n*Carlo Caputo (1897\u20131904 Appointed [[Apostolic Nuncio to Germany]])\n*Tommaso Cirielli (1899\u20131902 Died)<ref>Cirelli was appointed titular Bishop of Proconessos on 22 June 1899. He died on 26 February 1902. Serena, p. 334.</ref>\n*Carlo Giuseppe Cecchini, [[Order of Preachers|O.P.]] (1904\u20131909 Appointed [[Archbishop of Taranto]])\n*Adolfo Verrienti (1910\u20131929 Resigned)\n*Domenico Dell'Aquila (1932\u20131942 Died)\n*Giuseppe Della Cioppa (1943\u20131947 Appointed [[Bishop of Alife]])\n\n===Territorial Prelature of Altamura ed Acquaviva delle Fonti===\n''Name Changed: 17 August 1848''<br>\n''Latin Name: Altamurensis et Aquavievensis''<br>\n''Metropolitan: [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Bari-Bitonto|Archdiocese of Bari-Canosa]]''\n\n*Salvatore Rotolo, [[S.D.B.]] (1948\u20131962 Retired)\n*Antonio D'Erchia (1962\u20131964 Appointed [[Bishop of Conversano|Apostolic Administrator of Conversano]])\n*Salvatore Isgr\u00f3 (1975\u20131982 Appointed [[Archbishop of Sassari]])\n*Tarcisio Pisani, [[Order of the Minims|O.M.]] (1982\u20131986 Appointed [[Bishop of Altamura-Gravina-Acquaviva delle Fonti]])\n\n===Diocese of Altamura-Gravina-Acquaviva delle Fonti===\n''30 September 1986: United with the [[Diocese of Gravina]]''<br>\n''Latin Name: Altamurensis-Gravinensis-Aquavievensis''\n\n*Agostino Superbo (1994\u20131997 Resigned)\n*Mario Paciello (1997\u20132013 Retired)\n*[[Giovanni Ricchiuti]] (2013\u2013 )\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n==Books==\n*{{cite book|last=Ciccimarra|first=Nicola|title=La Cattedrale di Altamura: monumento di vita, di fede, di arte|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=8_1fPQAACAAJ|year=1964|publisher=Cressati|location=Altamura|language=Italian}}\n*{{cite book|editor=Cordasco, Pasquale|title=Le pergamene della cattedrale di Altamura (1309-1381)|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=CijkAAAAMAAJ|year=1994|publisher=Societ\u00e0 di storia patria per la Puglia|location=Bari|language=Italian, Latin}}\n*{{cite book|last=Giannone|first=Pietro|title=Istoria civile del regno di Napoli|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=YkU-AAAAcAAJ&pg=PA454|volume=Volume quinto (5)|year=1821|publisher=Nicol\u00f2 Bettoni|location=Milano|language=Italian|pages=454\u2013459}}\n*{{cite book|last=Giustiniani|first=Lorenzo|title=Dizionario geografico ragionato del Regno di Napoli|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=-9NsfnEzzjgC&pg=PA133|volume=Tom. I|year=1797|publisher=Vincenzo Manfredi|location=Napoli|language=Italian|pages=125\u2013136}}\n*{{cite book|last=Serena|first=Ottavio|title=La chiesa di Altamura: la serie dei suoi prelati e le sue iscrizioni|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=WK7ztgAACAAJ|year=1902|location=Trani|language=Italian}}\n* Serena, Ottavio (1902). [http://www.internetculturale.it/jmms/iccuviewer/iccu.jsp?id=oai%3Awww.internetculturale.sbn.it%2FTeca%3A20%3ANT0000%3ARML0064697_189893&mode=all&teca=MagTeca+-+ICCU&fulltext=1 \"La chiesa di Altamura, la serie dei suoi prelati e le sue iscrizioni\"], in: ''Rassegna pugliese di scienze lettere ed arti'' 19, nos. 11-12 (1902), pp.&nbsp;322\u2013337.\n\n===Acknowledgment===\n{{Catholic}}\n\n{{multiple image\n|align=center\n|footer=Co-cathedrals: Gravina Cathedral (left), and Acquaviva Cathedral (right)\n|image1=Gravina in Puglia - Vista della Cattedrale.jpg\n|width1=280\n|image2=Acquaviva delle Fonti - Cathedral 1.jpg\n|width2=205\n}}\n\n{{Roman Catholic Ecclesiastical Province of Bari-Bitonto}}\n\n{{coord|40.8167|N|16.5500|E|source:wikidata-and-enwiki-cat-tree_region:IT|display=title}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Roman Catholic dioceses in Apulia|Altamura]]\n[[Category:Religious organizations established in the 1240s]]\n[[Category:Dioceses established in the 13th century|Altamura]]\n[[Category:Altamura|Diocese]]\n", "text_old": "{{refimprove|date=October 2016}}\n{{Infobox diocese\n| jurisdiction      = Diocese<!-- Type of jurisdiction: i.e. Diocese or Archdiocese -->\n| name              = Altamura-Gravina-Acquaviva delle Fonti\n| latin             = Dioecesis Altamurensis-Gravinensis-Aquavievensis\n| local             = <!-- Name in the native language --> \n| image             = Puglia Altamura1 tango7174.jpg\n| image_size        = 255px\n| image_alt         = \n| caption           = Cathedral in [[Altamura]]\n<!---- Locations ---->\n| country           = {{flag|Italy}}\n| metropolitan      =  \n| territory         = \n| province          = [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Bari-Bitonto|Bari-Bitonto]]\n| coordinates       = <!-- Use {{coord}} --> \n<!---- Statistics ---->\n| area_km2          = 1,309 \n| population        = 172,400 (est.)\n| population_as_of  = 2015\n| catholics         = 170,400 (est.)<!-- Number of Catholics in the diocese -->\n| catholics_percent = 98.8\n| parishes          = 40<!-- Number of parishes in the diocese -->\n| churches          = <!-- Number of churches in the diocese -->\n| congregations     = <!-- Number of congregations in the diocese -->\n| schools           = <!-- Number of church supported schools in the diocese -->\n| members           = <!-- Number of members in the diocese -->\n<!---- Information ---->\n| denomination      = [[Catholic Church]]\n| rite              = [[Roman Rite]]\n| established       = 1248\n| cathedral         = [[Altamura Cathedral|Cattedrale di S. Maria Assunta]]\n| cocathedral       =  Basilica Concattedrale di Maria SS. Assunta<br>[[Acquaviva Cathedral|Concattedrale di S. Eustachio]]\n| patron            = \n| priests           = 68 (diocesan)<br />22 (Religious Orders)<br />11 Deacons<!-- Number of priests in the diocese -->\n<!---- Current leadership ---->\n| pope              = {{Incumbent pope}} <!-- DO NOT CHANGE. This will update the Popes Automatically as they change -->\n| bishop_title      = Bishop\n| bishop            = [[Mario Paciello]]\n| coadjutor         = \n| auxiliary_bishops = \n| vicar_general     = \n| emeritus_bishops  = \n<!---- Map ---->\n| map               = Roman Catholic Diocese of Altamura in Italy.jpg\n| map_alt           = Locator map for diocese of Altamura\n| map_caption       = \n<!---- Website ---->\n| website           = \n| footnotes         = [http://www.diocesidialtamura.it/ www.diocesidialtamura.it]\n}}\n\nThe  '''Diocese of Altamura-Gravina-Acquaviva delle Fonti''' ({{lang-la|Dioecesis Altamurensis-Gravinensis-Aquavievensis}}) is a Roman Catholic [[diocese]] in [[Apulia]], southern Italy, created in 1986. In that year, the '''territorial prelature of Altamura e Acquaviva delle Fonti''' was united with the [[diocese of Gravina]]. The present diocese is a [[suffragan]] of the [[archdiocese of Bari-Bitonto]].<ref name=CathHierAltGravAcq>[http://www.catholic-hierarchy.org/diocese/dagaf.html \"Diocese of Altamura-Gravina-Acquaviva delle Fonti\"] ''[[Catholic-Hierarchy.org]]''. David M. Cheney. Retrieved September 30, 2016.{{Self-published inline|date=March 2017}}</ref><ref name=GCathAltGravAcq>[http://www.gcatholic.org/dioceses/diocese/alta0.htm \"Diocese of Altamura-Gravina-Acquaviva delle Fonti\"] ''GCatholic.org''. Gabriel Chow. Retrieved September 30, 2016.{{Self-published inline|date=March 2017}}</ref>\n\nThe seat of the bishop is at [[Altamura Cathedral]], with [[Acquaviva Cathedral]] and [[Gravina Cathedral]] as [[co-cathedral]]s.\n\n==History==\n\n[[Altamura]] was once a [[territorial prelature]]: an [[archipresbyterate]], declared exempt from episcopal jurisdiction by [[Pope Innocent IV]] in 1248, and again by [[Pope Innocent VIII]] (1484\u201392). [[Acquaviva delle Fonti]], a town of the Campagna, was declared similarly exempt by [[Pope Pius IX]] and united with Altamura on 17 August 1848.<ref>[http://www.newadvent.org/cathen/01345b.htm ''Catholic Encyclopedia'' article]</ref>\n\n==Prelates and Bishops==\n===Territorial Prelature of Altamura===\n''Erected: 1248''<br>\n''Latin Name: Altamurensis''\n:'''...'''\n*Pietro de Moreriis (1296 \u2013 c. 1308?)<ref>Pietro de Angeriaco was appointed by [[Charles II of Naples|Charles II of Anjou, King of Naples]] 1285\u20131309) in 1296. Charles II had successfully petitioned [[Pope Boniface VIII]] to unite the two offices of Treasurer of S. Nicholas in Bari and Archpriest of Altamura.  {{cite book|author=Antonio Beatillo|title=Historia della vita, miracoli, traslatione, e gloria dell'illustrissimo confessore di Christo San Nicol\u00f2 il Magno Arcivescovo di Mira|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=i0ZMAAAAcAAJ&pg=RA2-PA460|year=1703|publisher=Pietro Olivieri|location=Roma|language=Italian|page=460}} Serena, pp. 330-331.</ref>\n:'''...'''\n*Giovanni Geronimo de Mari (attested 1606\u20131607)<ref>{{cite book|author=Bartolomeo Chioccarelli|title=Archivio della reggia giurisdizione del regno di Napoli, ristretto in indice compendioso ...|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=tKhFAAAAcAAJ&pg=RA1-PA32|year=1721|location=Vinezia|language=Italian|pages=26\u201334; 132\u2013134}}</ref>\n:'''...'''\n*Giandomenico Falcone (1 June 1842 \u2013 10 July 1858 \u2013 24 December 1862)<ref>Canon Falcone had been Vicar General of Molfetta before being named Archpriest of Acquaviva on 1 June 1842 by King Ferdinand II of Naples. {{cite book|last=Michele Garruba|first=|title=Serie critica de sacri pastori Baresi, corr. accresciuta ed ill|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=nldcAAAAcAAJ&pg=PA42|year=1844|publisher=Cannone|location=Bari|language=Italian|page=711\u2013712}}  To this was added the office of Archpriest of Altamura on 16 October 1858: {{cite book|title=Almanacco reale del regno delle Due Sicilie|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Y6BjAAAAcAAJ&pg=PA176|year=1854|publisher=Stamperia Reale|location=Napoli|language=Italian|page=176}} On 10 July 1858 Falcone was named titular Bishop of Eumeneia: {{cite book|title=La civilt\u00e0 cattolica: pubblicazione periodica per tutta l'Italia|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=B9E0V4Pxh9AC&pg=PA229|series=Terza serie|volume=Vol. 11|year=1858|publisher=Uffizio della civilta cattolica|location=Roma|language=Italian|page=229}} Serena, p. 334.</ref>\n:''Sede Vacante'' (24 December 1862 \u2013 28 August 1879)\n*Luigi Marcello Pellegrini (1879\u20131894 Died)<ref>In May 1881 Pellegrini was appointed titular Bishop of Troas (Turkey). Serena, p. 334.</ref>\n*Carlo Caputo (1897\u20131904 Appointed [[Apostolic Nuncio to Germany]])\n*Tommaso Cirielli (1899\u20131902 Died)<ref>Cirelli was appointed titular Bishop of Proconessos on 22 June 1899. He died on 26 February 1902. Serena, p. 334.</ref>\n*Carlo Giuseppe Cecchini, [[Order of Preachers|O.P.]] (1904\u20131909 Appointed [[Archbishop of Taranto]])\n*Adolfo Verrienti (1910\u20131929 Resigned)\n*Domenico Dell'Aquila (1932\u20131942 Died)\n*Giuseppe Della Cioppa (1943\u20131947 Appointed [[Bishop of Alife]])\n\n===Territorial Prelature of Altamura ed Acquaviva delle Fonti===\n''Name Changed: 17 August 1848''<br>\n''Latin Name: Altamurensis et Aquavievensis''<br>\n''Metropolitan: [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Bari-Bitonto|Archdiocese of Bari-Canosa]]''\n\n*Salvatore Rotolo, [[S.D.B.]] (1948\u20131962 Retired)\n*Antonio D'Erchia (1962\u20131964 Appointed [[Bishop of Conversano|Apostolic Administrator of Conversano]])\n*Salvatore Isgr\u00f3 (1975\u20131982 Appointed [[Archbishop of Sassari]])\n*Tarcisio Pisani, [[Order of the Minims|O.M.]] (1982\u20131986 Appointed [[Bishop of Altamura-Gravina-Acquaviva delle Fonti]])\n\n===Diocese of Altamura-Gravina-Acquaviva delle Fonti===\n''30 September 1986: United with the [[Diocese of Gravina]]''<br>\n''Latin Name: Altamurensis-Gravinensis-Aquavievensis''\n\n*Agostino Superbo (1994\u20131997 Resigned)\n*Mario Paciello (1997\u20132013 Retired)\n*[[Giovanni Ricchiuti]] (2013\u2013 )\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n==Books==\n*{{cite book|last=Ciccimarra|first=Nicola|title=La Cattedrale di Altamura: monumento di vita, di fede, di arte|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=8_1fPQAACAAJ|year=1964|publisher=Cressati|location=Altamura|language=Italian}}\n*{{cite book|editor=Cordasco, Pasquale|title=Le pergamene della cattedrale di Altamura (1309-1381)|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=CijkAAAAMAAJ|year=1994|publisher=Societ\u00e0 di storia patria per la Puglia|location=Bari|language=Italian, Latin}}\n*{{cite book|last=Giannone|first=Pietro|title=Istoria civile del regno di Napoli|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=YkU-AAAAcAAJ&pg=PA454|volume=Volume quinto (5)|year=1821|publisher=Nicol\u00f2 Bettoni|location=Milano|language=Italian|pages=454\u2013459}}\n*{{cite book|last=Giustiniani|first=Lorenzo|title=Dizionario geografico ragionato del Regno di Napoli|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=-9NsfnEzzjgC&pg=PA133|volume=Tom. I|year=1797|publisher=Vincenzo Manfredi|location=Napoli|language=Italian|pages=125\u2013136}}\n*{{cite book|last=Serena|first=Ottavio|title=La chiesa di Altamura: la serie dei suoi prelati e le sue iscrizioni|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=WK7ztgAACAAJ|year=1902|location=Trani|language=Italian}}\n* Serena, Ottavio (1902). [http://www.internetculturale.it/jmms/iccuviewer/iccu.jsp?id=oai%3Awww.internetculturale.sbn.it%2FTeca%3A20%3ANT0000%3ARML0064697_189893&mode=all&teca=MagTeca+-+ICCU&fulltext=1 \"La chiesa di Altamura, la serie dei suoi prelati e le sue iscrizioni\"], in: ''Rassegna pugliese di scienze lettere ed arti'' 19, nos. 11-12 (1902), pp.&nbsp;322\u2013337.\n\n===Acknowledgment===\n{{Catholic}}\n\n{{multiple image\n|align=center\n|footer=Co-cathedrals: Gravina Cathedral (left), and Acquaviva Cathedral (right)\n|i