 '''Fengyuan Bus'''\n** 6609:Taipei\u2014Fengyuan\n* '''Hsinchu Bus'''\n** 9003:Taipei\uff0dHsinchu\n\n===Allowance of bus platforms===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align; margin:0 auto\"\n|-\n!Floor!!User!!Platform used!!Remark\n|-\n|2||{{plainlist|\n* Ubus\n* Kuo-Kuang Bus\n* Sanchong, Hsinchu}}\n|{{plainlist|\n* Ubus\uff1a2, 3, 6, 10, 16<ref>Platform 6 Temporary not in use</ref>\n* Kuo-Kuang Bus\uff1a11, 12, 13, 14, 15<ref>Platform 11 reserved</ref>\n*  Sanchong Hsinchu\uff1a8, 9}}\n|{{plainlist|\n* Platform1, 4 Closed\n* Platform 5, 7 for disembark of Kuo-Kuang Bus, Sanchong, Hsinchu}}\n|-\n|3\n|{{plainlist|\n* Ubus\n* How Tai}}\n|{{plainlist|\n* Ubus\uff1a2, 3, 11, 12, 13, 14, 15, 16\n* How Tai\uff1a10}}\n|{{plainlist|\n* Platform 1, 4, 5, 11 Closed\n* Platform6, 7, 8, 9 for disembarks}}\n|-\n|4\n|{{plainlist|\n* Ho Hsin\n* Aloha Bus\n* KML BUS\n* Fongyuan Bus}}\n|{{plainlist|\nHo Hsin\uff1a1, 2, 3, 4, 5\n* Aloha Bus\uff1a15, 16<ref>Platform 15 Temporary not in use</ref>\n* KML Bus\uff1a13, 14<ref>Platform 14 Temporary not in use</ref>\n* Fongyuan Bus\uff1a10||Platform7, 8, 9, 11, 12 for disembarks}}\n|-\n|}\n\n===Shopping Mall===\n* [[Qsquare]]: Operational area at 20,000 ping. Entrance is at Chengde Rd. Opened on 11 December 2009. Includes Vieshow Cinemas.\n\n===Business Hotel===\n* Palais de Chine\n\n===Residential===\nAbout 1,000 households provided.\n\n===Control Center===\n* [[Operations control center|OCC]] of [[Taipei Rapid Transit System|TRTC]](T9 OCC)\n* Traffic OCC of Taipei City Hall\n\n==See also==\n* [[Taipei City Hall Bus Station]]\n* [[Taipei Station]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Taipei Bus Station}}\n* [http://www.taipeibus.com.tw/ Taipei Bus Station] {{in lang|zh-tw}}\n* [http://www.jsl.com.tw/itaipei/ Jin-Jan i Taipei]\n* [http://www.radium.com.tw/ \u65e5\u52dd\u751f\u6d3b\u79d1\u6280]\n\n[[Category:2009 establishments in Taiwan]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in Taipei]]\n[[Category:Bus stations in Taiwan]]\n[[Category:Transportation in Taipei]]\n[[Category:Transport infrastructure completed in 2009]]\n", "text_old": "{{Coord|25|02|57.6|N|121|31|00.7|E|display=title}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2014}}\n{{Infobox station\n| name             = Taipei Bus Station\n| native_name      = \u53f0\u5317\u8f49\u904b\u7ad9\n| native_name_lang = zh-TW\n| image            = Taipei Bus Station under construction 20090704.jpg\n| alt              = \n| caption          = Taipei Bus Station\n| address          = \n| borough          = [[Datong District, Taipei|Datong]], [[Taipei]]\n| country          = Taiwan\n| latitude         = \n| longitude        = \n| distance         = \n| operator         = \n| line             = \n| platforms        = \n| connections      = \n| structure        = At-grade\n| disabled         = \n| code             =\n| opened           = 19 August 2009\n| passengers       = \n}}\n\nThe '''Taipei Bus Station''' ({{zh|c=\u53f0\u5317\u8f49\u904b\u7ad9|p=T\u00e1ib\u011bi Zhu\u01ceny\u00f9nzh\u00e0n}}) is a multi-use complex located next to [[Taipei Station]] in [[Datong District, Taipei|Datong District]], [[Taipei]], [[Taiwan]]. The complex houses the Taipei bus terminal station provided a number of intercity express bus routes which was inaugurated on 19 August 2009, as well as recreational and leisure facilities.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www2.dorts.gov.tw/news/newsletter/ns259/rp259_01.htm|title=\u300c\u4ea4\u4e5d\u300d\u958b\u767c\u6848\u7ae3\u5de5\u3000\u81fa\u5317\u8f49\u904b\u7ad9\u555f\u7528\u71df\u904b|publisher=Department of Rapid Transit Systems|date=1 September 2009|accessdate=20 June 2010}}</ref> The mall complex was inaugurated on 11 December 2009. The shopping mall part is called [[Qsquare]].\n\n==Facilities==\n[[Image:Taipei Bus Station entrance 20090820.jpg|thumb|right|300px|Taipei Bus Station entrance.]]\n\n===Intercity bus routes===\n* '''United Bus (UBus)'''\n** 1610\uff1aTaipei\uff0dKaohsung\n** 1611\uff1aTaipei\uf